# Component Patterns

## Common Components
Use shared components from [src/utils/common.jsx](mdc:src/utils/common.jsx):
- `Container` - Consistent max-width and padding
- `FadeIn` - Scroll-triggered fade animation
- `FadeInInitial` - Immediate fade animation

## Animation Patterns
- Use Framer Motion for complex animations
- Apply `Reveal` component for scroll-triggered reveals
- Use `AnimatePresence` for enter/exit animations
- Prefer `motion.div` over `div` when animations are needed

## Page Structure
Each page should follow this pattern:
```jsx
export default function PageName() {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-[var(--paper)]">
      <Container className="py-16">
        {/* Page content */}
      </Container>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Theme Integration
- Access theme state through props from App.jsx
- Use CSS variables for all colors
- Ensure proper contrast in both light and dark modes
- Test theme switching functionality

## Navigation
- Use React Router's `Link` component for internal navigation
- Apply consistent hover states: `hover:text-[var(--ink)]`
- Use `useLocation` for active state detection if needed

## Blog Integration
- Use `getRecentPosts()` and `getPostBySlug()` from [src/blog/blogUtils.js](mdc:src/blog/blogUtils.js)
- Apply `blog-content` class for markdown styling
- Use `resolvePostImage()` for image paths